    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>The diaries, 1849-1862, of 
         <persname>William M. Blackford</persname>are concerned with
         life in 
         <geogname>Lynchburg, Virginia</geogname>, his career, his
         family and related 
         <famname>Davis family</famname>and 
         <famname>Minor family</famname>, life at the 
         <corpname>University of Virginia</corpname>, and the
         experiences of his five sons in the 
         <corpname>Confederate States Army</corpname>. 
         <persname>William M. Blackford</persname>(1801-1864) was a
         editor, postmaster and bank cashier in 
         <geogname>Lynchburg</geogname>. 
         <archref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Volume 1 of the diaries is located in accession
         #2221</archref>.</p>
    </scopecontent>
